snippet.textDisplay: Damn those dislikes :( makes me sad. I know people wanted another third party characters but guys, Sakurai and his team worked really hard to brings us a complete Smash Bros game with everyone and then added 4 new DLC third party characters, do people not know how hard it is to get the copyright and contracts for a studio that has nothing to do with their own? All I'm saying is Sakurai works hard and doesn't take breaks and we shouldn't be too harsh on him for wanting to put one first party character in, even if it's a Fire Emblem character. They've done a lot more right in this game than wrong, something I can't say about other disappointing franchises with new DLC *cough cough*. I'm sure Sakurai had a lot more well wanted third parties for the next DLC pack and just added them there to make it look more attractive to players to buy.

I'm a BIG Fire Emblem fan, but I'm pretty iffy to this reveal. Byleth is cool and all, but theres a lotta problems going on:

Over flooded sword and Fire Emblem characters (we didnt need Chrom that bad)

The way they chose to reveal Byleth

Not giving him magic

Not adding him to the roster of the next 6 DLC after the first pack (AKA, poor timing)

Dante's hype (#DanteForSmash)

I know these points are kinda up for debate, but I think we should all accept the fact that there's still a chance for Dante to get in
